LAGOS – A Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) chieftain, Chief Emeka C. Kalu, has called for the speedy hearing of Senator Orji Uzor Kalu’s appeal to ensure that the people of Abia North he is representing will have a voice at the upper legislative chamber. Kalu, Director General (DG), Protocols, Peoples Democratic Party Youth Alliance (PDPYA), who spoke too Daily Independent in Lagos, said it was disheartening that since the former governor was jailed, nothing was being said or done about the Abia North seat. It would be recalled that a Federal High Court in Lagos recently handed down a 12- year jail term to former governor Orji Uzor Kalu over corruption related issues, including money laundering. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The people of Abia North senatorial district recently protested lack of representation in the Senate and urged political stakeholders in the state and the zone to do something about it so that they would have someone to speak for them and attract projects to the area.